A tool to parse and pretty-print JSON5.

Usage:

    $ echo '{foo:"bar"}' | python -m json5.tool
    {
        foo: 'bar',
    }
    $ echo '{foo:"bar"}' | python -m json5.tool --as-json
    {
        "foo": "bar"
    }

Example Usage:

    class Real:
        def __init__(self):
            self.prop1 = 'prop1_val'
        def method1(self):
            return "method1_val"

    class ProxyWrapped(Proxy):
        prop1 = 'proxy_prop1_val' #both get/set operations are overriden when declared at proxy level
        def method1(self):
            return "proxy_method1_val"

    proxyObj:Real = ProxyWrapped(Real())
    proxyObj.prop1 # "proxy_prop1_val"

